# Org verification with cursor-tagged test data

Whenever you implement or change Salesforce functionality in this project (Apex, LWC, Flow, triggers, quick actions), **verify it yourself in the org** before marking the task done. Do not rely only on unit tests or "deploy succeeded."

## Default org

- Target org alias: `gptfy-poc1` (`kesavpoc@gptfy.com`)
- Use `sf` CLI commands; do not ask the user to test unless org access fails

## Tag all test records with `cursor`

Every dummy record created for verification must include **`cursor`** in a searchable field so the user can find and clean up test data:

- **Case**: `Subject = 'cursor-test-{timestamp} {scenario description}'`
- **Knowledge article**: title inherits from Case Subject (already tagged)
- **Other objects**: prefix Name/Subject/Title with `cursor-test-{timestamp}`

Example timestamp format: `Datetime.now().format('yyyyMMdd-HHmmss')`

## How to verify

1. Deploy changed metadata if not already in the org
2. Write a script under `scripts/apex/` (e.g. `scripts/apex/test{FeatureName}.apex`)
3. Run: `sf apex run --file scripts/apex/test{FeatureName}.apex --target-org gptfy-poc1`
4. Query results: `sf data query --query "SELECT ... WHERE Subject LIKE 'cursor-test%'" --target-org gptfy-poc1`
5. Report back to the user:
   - What was tested (create / update / dedupe / error path)
   - Pass/fail for each assertion
   - Record Ids and direct Lightning URLs
   - The `cursor-test-...` marker string to search in the org

## Script template

```apex
String marker = 'cursor-test-' + Datetime.now().format('yyyyMMdd-HHmmss');
// 1. Create dummy data tagged with marker
// 2. Invoke the feature (Apex method, DML, etc.)
// 3. Query and System.debug assertions
// 4. System.debug('=== CURSOR TEST COMPLETE ===');
// 5. System.debug('Marker: ' + marker);
```

## When to skip

- Read-only questions or code review with no new behavior
- User explicitly says not to touch the org
- Change is docs-only or local tooling with no Salesforce runtime

## Leave test data in the org

Do not delete cursor-tagged records unless the user asks. They use these to inspect results manually.
